was focused primarily on HF or time domain measures. Although the use of HRV data from the 2-min rhythm strip led to the exclusion of a large proportion of our cohort, their characteristics were similar to those included (Online Table 2), and the results were robust on using 10-s ECG data with fewer exclusions. Last, we did not see an attenuation of effect estimates after excluding AF events during the initial 2 years of follow-up; thus, reverse causality is unlikely. Case ascertainment in the absence of continuous ambulatory ECG monitoring for paroxysmal AF and outpatient surveillance has lower sensitivity especially after 1998 (last visit with ﬁeld center ECG recordings) and remains another limitation, but speciﬁcity and positive predictive value of hospital diagnosis are high.
CONCLUSIONS
Our study found that a decrease in modulation of the heart rate was associated with an increased risk of new-onset AF. Modulation of ANS inputs have proven beneﬁcial among patients undergoing wide circumferential AF ablation. Whether interventions ranging from exercise and yoga to direct modulation of ANS can prevent AF in high- and moderate-risk individuals remains to be examined.

ACKNOWLEDGMENTS The authors thank the ARIC participants, staff, and investigators for their longterm contributions to ARIC.
REPRINT REQUESTS AND CORRESPONDENCE: Dr. Sunil K. Agarwal, Cardiovascular Institute, Mount Sinai School of Medicine, Guggenheim Pavilion, 1190 Fifth Avenue–1 West, New York, New York 10029. E-mail: sunilagarwal1@gmail.com.
PERSPECTIVES
COMPETENCY IN MEDICAL KNOWLEDGE: In a large, biracial, population-based cohort of middleaged men and women, impaired cardiac autonomic responsiveness, as reﬂected in a low HRV, was associated with an increased risk of AF independent of several traditional risk factors.
TRANSLATIONAL OUTLOOK: Future studies should investigate whether modulation of the ANS is effective in preventing AF. Candidate approaches include weight management, exercise, yoga, prevention or treatment of sleep apnea, or administration of adrenergic inhibitor drugs.

